  "texts": [
    "3.23Scale-Travel Parameters for DIVERSEVAR Scale-travel rewinds the autoregressive generation from stage l to stage m. In Tab.",
    "F.2, we vary l ∈ {6, 8, 10} and m ∈ {2, 3, 4}.",
    "We find that m = 3 and m = 4 yields the best diversity-quality tradeoff for Infinity and Switti, respectively.Temperature and Top-p samplingAutoregressive models can control the diversity of generation by varying the temperature τ and through nucleus (top-p) sampling.",
    "As shown in Tab.",
    "F.3, while increasing the temperature τ also increases the diversity, DIVERSEVAR achieves the highest diversity."
  ]
}